<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="granola" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Granola (Grandma Joy)</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>4 cups oats</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>1 \frac{1}{2}</m> cups sliced almonds</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup packed light brown sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>1 \frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoons cinnamon</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup canola oil</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup honey</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup dried cranberries</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup dried blueberries</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          In a large bowl, mix oats, almonds, brown sugar, salt, and cinnamon.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          In a small pan, warm the canola oil and honey. Whisk in vanilla.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Carefully pour over liquid over oat mixture, and Stir gently with a wooden spoon.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Spread granola in a 15'' x 10'' x 1'' pan, and bake at <m>300\circ</m> for 40 minutes.  Stir carefully every 10 minutes.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Transfer granola-filled pan to a wire rack and cool completely.  Stir in dried fruit.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Seal granola in an airtight container or self-sealing plastic bag.  Store at room temperature for a week or in the freezer for up to 3 months.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>